# GoMath

GoMath is an API which answers simple math problems

# Group Endpoints

## Add [/add{?input,input}]
+ Parameters
    + input: 1 (required, number) - Input number to add
    + input: 1 (required, number) - Input number to add

### Add two input numbers [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Header
        X-Transaction-ID: "Problem ID"
    + Body
        {
            "problem_id": "bdmb8cboo3smi6jgiai0",
            "operation": "addition",
            "input_1": 1,
            "input_2": 1,
            "answer": 2
        }
        
## Subtract [/subtract{?input,input}]
+ Parameters
    + input: 46 (required, number) - Input number to subtract from
    + input: 45 (required, number) - Input number to subtract by

### Subtract the second input number from the first [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Headers
        X-Transaction-ID: "Problem ID"
    + Body
        {
            "problem_id": "bdmb8cboo3smi6jgiai1",
            "operation": "subtraction",
            "input_1": 46,
            "input_2": 45,
            "answer": 1
        }

## Multiply [/multiply{?input,input}]
+ Parameters
    + input: 3 (required, number) - Input number to multiply
    + input: 4 (required, number) - Input number to multiply

### Multiply the first two input numbers together [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Headers
        X-Transaction-ID: "Problem ID"
    + Body
        {
            "problem_id": "bdmb8cboo3smi6jgiai2",
            "operation": "multiplication",
            "input_1": 3,
            "input_2": 4,
            "answer": 12
        }

## Divide [/divide{?input,input}]
+ Parameters
    + input: 12 (required, number) - Input number to divide
    + input: 4 (required, number) - Input number to divide from

### Divide the first input number by the second [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Headers
        X-Transaction-ID: "Problem ID"
    + Body
        {
            "problem_id": "bdmb8cboo3smi6jgiai3",
            "operation": "division",
            "input_1": 12,
            "input_2": 4,
            "answer": 3
        }

## Problems [/problems]
